        "founder_story": {
            "type": "bonpet-founder-story",
            "settings": {
                "body": "<p>Nic's cats Salt and Pepper. Yash's dog Lola. Two software engineers, both frustrated that every Singapore pet food brand hid behind marketing fluff. No real ingredient lists. No real answers.</p><p>So we started cooking weekends in our own kitchens. Testing on our own furkids. Crashing at 6am, then dragging ourselves to day jobs. The work felt meaningful in a way day jobs hadn't, and our pets were visibly thriving. Friends started asking for packs.</p><p>In 2024 we rented an industrial kitchen on Pioneer Crescent and went all-in. Same recipes, same standards, same commitment: nothing in the pack we wouldn't feed Salt, Pepper, or Lola. From day one, every ingredient, every gram, every supplement has been published openly in a public Google Sheet. No proprietary blends. No marketing spin. The only way we know how to do this right.</p>"
            }
        },
